3月2日，保罗是九位投票反对一项临时法案的参议员之一，该法案从预算中削减了40亿美元，并将暂时阻止[[美国政府停摆|政府停摆]]，他说这项法案没有从预算中削减足够的资金<ref>{{cite web |last=Middleton |first=Neil |title=Yarmuth and Paul vote no on stopgap spending bill |website=WYMT-TV|date=2011-03-02 |url=http://www.wkyt.com/blogs/neilsnotebook/Yarmuth_and_Paul_vote_no_on_stopgap_GOP_spending_bill_117271378.html |access-date=2021-01-18 |dead-url=yes |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110718072456/http://www.wkyt.com/blogs/neilsnotebook/Yarmuth_and_Paul_vote_no_on_stopgap_GOP_spending_bill_117271378.html |archive-date=2011-07-18}}</ref>。一周后，他投票反对民主党和共和党继续为联邦政府提供资金的预算提案，称两项法案都没有削减足够的开支。这两项法案都未能在参议院通过。他后来在3月17日和4月8日投票反对权宜之计，而这两项议案都在参议院获得通过<ref>{{cite web |last=Jaffe |first=Matthew |title=Kickin' the Can: Senate Passes Stop-Gap Spending Plan, Buys Lawmakers Three More Weeks To Solve Funding Mess |website=ABC News |date=2011-03-17 |url=http://blogs.abcnews.com/thenote/2011/03/kickin-the-can-senate-passes-stop-gap-spending-plan-buys-lawmakers-three-more-weeks-to-solve-funding.html |access-date=2021-01-18 |archive-date=2017-08-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170803050118/http://blogs.abcnews.com/thenote/2011/03/kickin-the-can-senate-passes-stop-gap-spending-plan-buys-lawmakers-three-more-weeks-to-solve-funding.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Wong |first=Scott |title=Rand Paul opposes temporary stopgap |work=Politico |date=2011-04-09 |url=http://www.politico.com/blogs/glennthrush/0411/Rand_Paul_opposes_temporary_stopgap_.html |access-date=2021-01-18 |archive-date=2014-08-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140823090419/http://www.politico.com/blogs/glennthrush/0411/Rand_Paul_opposes_temporary_stopgap_.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

