2013年3月，保罗与参议员[[泰德·克鲁兹|泰德·克鲁兹]]和[[麥克·李_(美国政治家)|迈克·李]]扬言要进行另一次冗长演说，意图反对任何扩大联邦[[枪支管制|枪支管制]]措施的立法提案<ref>{{cite web |last=Allen |first=Jonathan |title=Rand Paul and Ted Cruz threaten filibuster on guns |url=http://www.politico.com/story/2013/03/rand-paul-and-ted-cruz-threaten-filibuster-on-guns-89299.html |work=Politico |access-date=2021-02-07 |date=2013-03-25 |archive-date=2021-01-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210105064547/https://www.politico.com/story/2013/03/rand-paul-and-ted-cruz-threaten-filibuster-on-guns-089299 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。这一冗长演说于2013年4月11日进行，但在68票对31票的投票中结束辩论<ref>{{cite web |title=Gun bill clears Senate hurdle as filibuster falls short |url=http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2013/04/11/gun-bill-clears-senate-hurdle-as-filibuster-falls-short |work=Fox News |date=2013-04-11 |accessdate=2021-02-07 |archive-date=2015-04-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150418013419/http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2013/04/11/gun-bill-clears-senate-hurdle-as-filibuster-falls-short/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。同样在2013年3月，保罗支持了肯塔基州的共和党参议员[[米奇·麦康奈尔|米奇·麦康奈尔]]{{le|2014年肯塔基州美国参议院选举|2014 United States Senate election in Kentucky|2014年的竞选连任}}<ref name="McConnell">{{cite news |first1=Nicole |last1=Vas |access-date=2021-02-07 |title=McConnell eyes Trump, Paul and reelection when it comes to emergency fight |url=https://thehill.com/homenews/senate/432568-mcconnell-eyes-trump-paul-and-reelection-when-it-comes-to-emergency-fight |date=2019-03-05 |website=The Hill |archive-date=2020-11-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201107233307/https://thehill.com/homenews/senate/432568-mcconnell-eyes-trump-paul-and-reelection-when-it-comes-to-emergency-fight |dead-url=no }}</ref>。麦康奈尔此前曾聘请保罗的2010年竞选经理{{le|杰西·本顿|Jesse Benton}}担任自己的竞选经理<ref name="Nat Review">{{cite web |last=Trinko |first=Katrina |title=From Rand to Mitch |url=http://www.nationalreview.com/article/354807/rand-mitch-katrina-trinko |access-date=2021-02-07 |newspaper=National Review |date=2014-07-31 |archive-date=2017-05-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170523174340/http://www.nationalreview.com/article/354807/rand-mitch-katrina-trinko |dead-url=no }}</ref>。保罗的支持被视为麦康奈尔避免在共和党初选中面临挑战的重大胜利<ref name=McConnell/>。

针对[[底特律|底特律]][[底特律破产|宣布破产]]，保罗表示，他不会允许政府试图救助底特律。2013年7月19日，保罗在接受《[[布赖特巴特新闻网|布赖特巴特新闻]]》的电话采访时说：“我基本上是说他是在为我的尸体提供救助，因为我们在华盛顿没有任何钱。”保罗说，他认为联邦救助会向其他有财政问题的城市发出错误的信息。<ref>{{cite web |last=Arkin |first=James |title=Rand Paul: No government bailout for Detroit |url=http://www.politico.com/story/2013/07/detroit-bankruptcy-bailout-rand-paul-94478.html |work=Politico |access-date=2021-02-07 |date=2013-07-19 |archive-date=2015-06-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150626225613/http://www.politico.com/story/2013/07/detroit-bankruptcy-bailout-rand-paul-94478.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

同年9月，保罗表示，美国应避免对正在进行的[[叙利亚内战|叙利亚内战]]进行军事干预<ref>{{cite web |last=Clary |first=Greg |title=Rand Paul: U.S. involvement in Syria a 'mistake |url=http://politicalticker.blogs.cnn.com/2013/09/01/rand-paul-u-s-involvement-in-syria-a-mistake/ |website=CNN |access-date=2021-02-07 |date=2013-09-01 |archive-date=2021-01-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210105064602/https://politicalticker.blogs.cnn.com/2013/09/01/rand-paul-u-s-involvement-in-syria-a-mistake/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。在一则[[社论对页版|评论版]]中，保罗反驳了奥巴马政府的说法，即军事力量的威胁导致叙利亚政府考虑交出化学武器，相反，他认为反对在叙利亚采取军事行动及其造成的拖延导致了外交进展<ref>{{cite news |last=Blake |first=Aaron |title=Rand Paul: Opposition to military action led to Syria diplomacy |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/post-politics/wp/2013/09/13/rand-paul-opposition-to-military-action-led-to-syria-diplomacy/ |newspaper=The Washington Post |access-date=2021-02-07 |date=2013-09-13 |archive-date=2015-05-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150513205538/http://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/post-politics/wp/2013/09/13/rand-paul-opposition-to-military-action-led-to-syria-diplomacy/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

2013年10月，有人发现保罗抄袭了[[维基百科|维基百科]]上支持{{le|2013年弗吉尼亚州州长选举|2013 Virginia gubernatorial election|弗吉尼亚州州长候选人}}{{le|肯·库奇内利|Ken Cuccinelli}}一篇演讲的其中一部分，这使得保罗成为了一些争议的对象。保罗引用了《[[千钧一发_(电影)|千钧一发]]》这部电影，几乎一字不差地引用了维基百科关于这部电影的文章，但没有引用片源<ref name=102813eug>{{cite news |last=Carroll |first=James R. |title=Sen. Rand Paul warns science could be used to alter gene pool |url=http://www.courier-journal.com/article/20131028/NEWS01/310280057/Sen-Rand-Paul-warns-science-abortion-could-used-eliminate-undesirables |newspaper=The Courier-Journal |location=Louisville, Kentucky|access-date=2021-02-07 |date=2013-10-28}}</ref><ref name=maddowread>{{cite web |last=Yarvitz |first=Michael |title=The Rand Paul plagiarism read-along! |url=https://www.msnbc.com/msnbc/catching-rand-paul-plagiarizing-home-edition |work=The Rachel Maddow Show |publisher=MSNBC |date=2013-10-29 |accessdate=2021-02-07 |archive-date=2013-12-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131204182958/http://www.msnbc.com/msnbc/catching-rand-paul-plagiarizing-home-edition |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=politifactgattaca>{{cite web |last1=Contorno |first1=Steve |last2=Kliegman |first2=Julie |title=Rachel Maddow says Rand Paul's 'Gattaca' speech 'was totally ripped off of Wikipedia|url=http://www.politifact.com/punditfact/statements/2013/nov/01/rachel-maddow/rachel-maddow-says-rand-pauls-gattaca-speech-was-t/ |website=PolitiFact |date=2013-11-01|accessdate=2021-02-07 |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200815102232/https://www.politifact.com/factchecks/2013/nov/01/rachel-maddow/rachel-maddow-says-rand-pauls-gattaca-speech-was-t/ |archive-date=2020-08-15}}</ref>。证据很快浮出水面，保罗在其他一些演讲中几乎一字不差地抄袭了其他作者的句子，而没有对原始来源给予赞扬<ref name="pounce">{{cite web |last=Miller |first=Jake |title=Critics pounce on Rand Paul's borrowed language |url=http://www.cbsnews.com/8301-250_162-57610423/critics-pounce-on-rand-pauls-borrowed-language/ |website=CBS News|date=2013-11-01 |accessdate=2021-02-07|dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190120111704/https://www.cbsnews.com/news/critics-pounce-on-rand-pauls-borrowed-language/ | archive-date=2020-01-20}}</ref><ref name=nyt110413>{{cite news |last=Martin |first=Jonathan |title=Senator Rand Paul faces new charges of plagiarism |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2013/11/05/us/politics/senator-rand-paul-faces-new-charges-of-plagiarism.html |newspaper=The New York Times |date=2013-11-04 |accessdate=2021-02-07 |archive-date=2017-05-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170518055736/http://www.nytimes.com/2013/11/05/us/politics/senator-rand-paul-faces-new-charges-of-plagiarism.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>，包括在他作为茶党反驳总统{{le|2013年国情咨文|2013 State of the Union Address}}的演讲中。此外，保罗的书《{{le|政府恶霸|Government Bullies}}》中长达三页的一段话直接取自保守派智库[[美国传统基金会|传统基金会]]的一篇文章<ref name=kaz3pgs>{{cite web |last=Kaczynski |first=Andrew |title=Three pages of Rand Paul's book were plagiarized from think tanks |url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/andrewkaczynski/entire-section-of-rand-pauls-book-copied-verbatim-from-case |website=BuzzFeed |date=2013-11-02|accessdate=2021-02-07 |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200828203732/https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/andrewkaczynski/entire-section-of-rand-pauls-book-copied-verbatim-from-case |archive-date=2020-08-28}}</ref><ref name=kazad>{{cite web |last=Kaczynski |first=Andrew |title=More instances of plagiarism in Rand Paul's book |url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/andrewkaczynski/more-instances-of-plagiarism-in-rand-pauls-book-lets-duel |website=BuzzFeed|accessdate=2021-02-07 |date=2013-11-07 |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191017223256/https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/andrewkaczynski/more-instances-of-plagiarism-in-rand-pauls-book-lets-duel |archive-date=2019-10-17}}</ref>。很明显，保罗在《[[华盛顿时报|华盛顿时报]]》上发表的关于强制性最低限额的评论文章以及他在参议院司法委员会上所作的相关证词，都包含了与几天前另一位作者发表的一篇文章几乎完全相同的材料<ref name=kazoped>{{cite web |last=Kaczynski |first=Andrew |title=Sections of Rand Paul's op-ed on drug sentencing plagiarized from article week earlier |url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/andrewkaczynski/sections-of-rand-pauls-op-ed-on-drug-sentencing-plagiarized |website=BuzzFeed|date=2013-11-04 |accessdate=2021-02-07|dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200605094525/https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/andrewkaczynski/sections-of-rand-pauls-op-ed-on-drug-sentencing-plagiarized |archive-date=2020-06-05}}</ref>，《华盛顿时报》说，该报将不再刊登保罗为该报撰稿的每周专栏文章<ref name=column>{{cite news |last=Blake |first=Aaron |title=After plagiarism allegations, Rand Paul's Washington Times column nixed |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/post-politics/wp/2013/11/06/after-plagiarism-allegations-rand-pauls-washington-times-column-nixed/ |newspaper=The Washington Post|date=2013-11-06 |accessdate=2021-02-07|dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200526145736if_/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/post-politics/wp/2013/11/06/after-plagiarism-allegations-rand-pauls-washington-times-column-nixed/?arc404=true |archive-date=2020-05-26}}</ref>。一周来，几乎每天都有关于抄袭新指控的新闻报道，保罗说，他受到了“不公平的标准”的约束，但他会重组他的办公室，以防止将来出现错误，如果这是“让人们离开我的地狱”所需要的<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2013/11/06/us/politics/after-plagiarism-charges-paul-announces-office-restructuring.html |title=After Plagiarism Charges, Paul Announces Office Restructuring |last1=Rutenberg |first1=Jim |last2=Parker |first2=Ashley |date=2013-11-05 |newspaper=The New York Times |access-date=2021-02-07 |dead-url=no |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191007233917/https://www.nytimes.com/2013/11/06/us/politics/after-plagiarism-charges-paul-announces-office-restructuring.html |archive-date=2019-10-07}}</ref>。

针对2014年初[[乌克兰亲欧盟示威运动|乌克兰政局动荡]]，保罗最初表示，美国应该继续铭记这样一个事实：尽管[[冷战|冷战]]已经结束，但俄罗斯仍然是拥有远程核导弹的军事大国。他说，美国应努力保持“与俄罗斯的尊重关系”，避免采取俄罗斯人可能认为是挑衅的行动，例如寻求乌克兰加入[[北约|北约]]或以其他方式干涉俄罗斯与乌克兰的关系。<ref name=tweakRussia>{{cite news |last=Costa |first=Robert |title=Rand Paul: GOP shouldn't 'tweak' Russia over Ukraine |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/post-politics/wp/2014/02/25/rand-paul-gop-shouldnt-tweak-russia-over-ukraine/ |newspaper=The Washington Post |date=2014-02-25 |accessdate=2021-02-12 |archive-date=2015-06-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150618135204/http://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/post-politics/wp/2014/02/25/rand-paul-gop-shouldnt-tweak-russia-over-ukraine/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

两周后，[[俄罗斯议会|俄罗斯议会]]批准在乌克兰使用军事力量<ref name=dumatroops>{{cite news |last1=Lally |first1=Kathy |last2=Englund |first2=Will |last3=Booth |first3=William |title=Russian parliament approves use of troops in Ukraine |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/europe/russian-parliament-approves-use-of-troops-in-crimea/2014/03/01/d1775f70-a151-11e3-a050-dc3322a94fa7_story.html |newspaper=The Washington Post |date=2014-03-01 |accessdate=2021-02-12 |archive-date=2021-02-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210201075937/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/europe/russian-parliament-approves-use-of-troops-in-crimea/2014/03/01/d1775f70-a151-11e3-a050-dc3322a94fa7_story.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>，俄罗斯总统[[弗拉基米尔·普京|弗拉基米尔·普京]]下令在俄罗斯与乌克兰的边境地区举行军事演习<ref name=putintroops>{{cite news |last1=Higgins |first1=Andrew |title=Putin orders drills in Crimea, clash shows region's divide |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/02/27/world/europe/russia.html |newspaper=The New York Times |date=2014-02-26 |last2=Myers |first2=Steven Lee |accessdate=2021-02-12 |archive-date=2020-11-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112025441/http://www.nytimes.com/2014/02/27/world/europe/russia.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>，保罗开始采取不同的态度<ref>{{cite news |last1=Hook |first1=Janet |title=GOP hawks are on the rise |url=https://online.wsj.com/news/articles/SB10001424052702304732804579421650599529822 |newspaper=The Wall Street Journal |date=2014-03-05 |last2=O'Connor |first2=Patrick |accessdate=2021-02-12 |archive-date=2014-08-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140823090507/http://online.wsj.com/news/articles/SB10001424052702304732804579421650599529822 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。他写道：“弗拉基米尔·普京入侵乌克兰是对乌克兰主权的严重侵犯，也是对国际社会的侮辱……普京必须因违反《[[布达佩斯安全保障备忘录|布达佩斯备忘录]]》而受到惩罚，俄罗斯必须了解，如果美国坚持表现得像一个流氓国家，它将孤立俄罗斯。”<ref name=Putinsaggression>{{cite magazine |last=Paul |first=Rand |title=U.S. must take strong action against Putin's aggression |url=http://time.com/17648/sen-rand-paul-u-s-must-take-strong-action-against-putins-aggression/ |magazine=TIME |date=2014-03-09 |accessdate=2021-02-12 |archive-date=2017-06-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170617005113/http://time.com/17648/sen-rand-paul-u-s-must-take-strong-action-against-putins-aggression/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>他说，美国和欧洲盟国可以对俄罗斯的军事侵略进行报复，但无需采取任何军事行动<ref name=Putinsaggression />。他敦促美国对俄罗斯实施经济制裁，并恢复{{le|美国在波兰的导弹防御系统|United States missile defense complex in Poland|在波兰和捷克共和国建设防御性反导设施}}的努力<ref name=Putinsaggression />。他还呼吁美国采取措施，以抵消俄罗斯对欧洲油气供应的战略影响，比如取消对美国新勘探和钻探化石燃料的限制，同时立即批准有争议的[[拱心石输油管道|拱心石输油管道]]，他说，这将使美国能够在俄罗斯试图切断对欧洲的石油和天然气供应情况下，向欧洲输送更多的石油和天然气<ref name=Putinsaggression />。

保罗在阻止与瑞士签订一项使国税局能够进行[[瑞士信贷集团|逃税调查]]的条约方面发挥了主导作用，保罗认为该条约将侵犯美国人的隐私<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.politico.com/story/2014/03/rand-paul-tax-swiss-banks-104148.html |title=Rand Paul in cross hairs of tax evasion war |last1=Bade |first1=Rachael |date=2014-03-02 |work=Politico |access-date=2021-02-12 |archive-date=2015-08-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150821074212/http://www.politico.com/story/2014/03/rand-paul-tax-swiss-banks-104148.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。保罗因其公共政策工作获得了[[国家利益中心|国家利益中心]]（正式名称为尼克松中心）颁发的2014年杰出服务奖<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://cftni.org/recent-events/2014-distinguished-service-award-dinner-honoring-senator-rand-paul/ |title=2014 Distinguished Service Award Dinner Honoring Senator Rand Paul |website=Center for the National Interest |access-date=2021-02-12 |archive-date=2020-12-01 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201201201342/https://cftni.org/recent-events/2014-distinguished-service-award-dinner-honoring-senator-rand-paul/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://nationalinterest.org/feature/rand-paul-the-case-conservative-realism-11544 |title=Rand Paul: The Case for Conservative Realism |last=Paul |first=Rand |date=2014-10-23 |website=The National Interest |language=en |access-date=2021-02-12 |archive-date=2020-12-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201216145748/https://nationalinterest.org/feature/rand-paul-the-case-conservative-realism-11544 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

针对有关[[中情局|中情局]]渗透到参议院情报委员会电脑的报道，保罗呼吁解雇中情局局长[[约翰·歐文·布伦南|约翰·布伦南]]<ref>{{cite web |last1=Everett |first1=Burgess |title=Rand Paul: Fire Brennan |url=http://www.politico.com/story/2014/08/rand-paul-fire-john-brennan-cia-109661.html?hp=r4 |website=Politico |date=2014-08 |access-date=2021-02-12 |archive-date=2014-08-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140812201627/http://www.politico.com/story/2014/08/rand-paul-fire-john-brennan-cia-109661.html?hp=r4 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。2014年12月，保罗支持奥巴马政府采取行动，改变美国对[[古巴|古巴]]的政策，放宽对古巴的贸易限制<ref>{{cite web |last1=Weigel |first1=Dave |title=Rand Paul Battles Marco Rubio Over Cuba Policy |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/politics/articles/2014-12-19/rand-paul-battles-marco-rubio-over-cuba-policy |website=Bloomberg L.P. |access-date=2021-02-12 |date=2014-12-19 |archive-date=2015-03-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150330082249/https://www.bloomberg.com/politics/articles/2014-12-19/rand-paul-battles-marco-rubio-over-cuba-policy |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

===第114届国会（2015－2017年）===
2015年初，参议员保罗重新提出了《{{le|美联储透明度法案|Federal Reserve Transparency Act}}》<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.randpac.com/2015/01/28/sen-paul-proposes-audit-federal-reserve/ |title=Sen. Paul Proposes an Audit of the Federal Reserve |website=Rand PAC |access-date=2021-01-31 |date=2015-01-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150204101808/http://www.randpac.com/2015/01/28/sen-paul-proposes-audit-federal-reserve/ |archive-date=2015-02-04 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。保罗还提出了《第五修正案完整性恢复法案》（{{lang|en|Fifth Amendment Integrity Restoration Act}}），该法案将限制{{le|资产没收|Asset forfeiture|民事没收}}程序<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.randpac.com/2015/01/27/sen-rand-paul-introduces-fair-act/ |title=Sen. Rand Paul Introduces the FAIR Act |date=2015-01-27 |access-date=2021-01-31 |website=Rand PAC |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150204123258/http://www.randpac.com/2015/01/27/sen-rand-paul-introduces-fair-act/ |archive-date=2015-02-04 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。为了反对《[[美国爱国者法案|爱国者法案]]》{{le|爱国者法案第二编第二节摘要|Section summary of the Patriot Act, Title II#Section 215: Access to records and other items under FISA|第215条}}的重新授权，保罗于2015年5月20日发表了10个半小时的讲话<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kim |first1=Seung Min |last2=Byers |first2=Alex |title=Rand Paul calls it a night after 10 1/2 hours |url=http://www.politico.com/story/2015/05/rand-paul-filibuster-patriot-act-118141.html |website=Politico |access-date=2021-01-31 |archive-date=2015-08-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150822055821/http://www.politico.com/story/2015/05/rand-paul-filibuster-patriot-act-118141.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2015/05/21/politics/rand-paul-nsa-patriot-act-fillibuster/index.html|title=Rand Paul seizes political moment with NSA protest|first1=Stephen|last1=Collinson|first2=Jeremy|last2=Diamond|work=CNN|date=2015-05-22|access-date=2021-01-31|archive-date=2021-01-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210126034717/https://edition.cnn.com/2015/05/21/politics/rand-paul-nsa-patriot-act-fillibuster/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。爱国者法案的条款在6月1日被禁止重新授权<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/live/2015/may/31/nsa-patriot-act-surveillance-reform-usa-freedom-live|title=NSA reform advances as Senate moves to vote on USA Freedom Act – as it happened|first1=Ben|last1=Jacobs|first2=Dan|last2=Roberts|first3=Spencer|last3=Ackerman|first4=Trevor|last4=Timm|date=2015-06-01|newspaper=The Guardian|access-date=2021-01-31|archive-date=2021-01-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210105064559/https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/live/2015/may/31/nsa-patriot-act-surveillance-reform-usa-freedom-live|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2016年2月15日，[[安东宁·斯卡利亚|安东宁·斯卡利亚]]去世后，保罗表示，他将反对奥巴马总统提出的任何取代已故最高法院大法官的提名。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://thinkprogress.org/politics/2016/02/15/3749689/rand-paul-scalia-supreme-court-obama-nominee/ |first=Emily |last=Atkin |title=Rand Paul: It's A 'Conflict Of Interest' For Obama To Nominate A Supreme Court Justice |date=2016-02-15 |accessdate=2021-01-31 |website=ThinkProgress.org |archive-date=2016-08-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160802160338/http://thinkprogress.org/politics/2016/02/15/3749689/rand-paul-scalia-supreme-court-obama-nominee/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

